{"abstract": "A generation of Indian energy entrepreneurs is out to prove that a fast, clean and economical route to universal electrification is through solar home systems, financed with small bank loans.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/03/business/energy-environment/electrifying-india-with-the-sun-and-small-loans.html", "snippet": "A generation of Indian energy entrepreneurs is out to prove that a fast, clean and economical route to universal electrification is through solar home systems, financed with small bank loans.", "lead_paragraph": "A few years ago, the hundred or so residents of Paradeshappanamatha, a secluded hamlet in the southern Indian state of Karnataka, gathered along the central pathway between their 22 densely clustered homes, and watched as government workers hoisted a solar-powered streetlamp. {"abstract": "Sidney Weinberg, \u201cMr. Wall Street,\u201d began a tradition of Goldman executives taking on public service that is continuing under President-elect Trump.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/01/business/dealbook/the-guys-from-government-sachs.html", "snippet": "Sidney Weinberg, \u201cMr. Wall Street,\u201d began a tradition of Goldman executives taking on public service that is continuing under President-elect Trump.", "lead_paragraph": "During World War II, President Franklin D.
